TY  - JOUR
AU  - Jovanovic, Boyan
T1  - Micro Shocks and Aggregate Risk*
PY  - 1987
Y1  - 1987/05/01
DO  - 10.2307/1885069
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 102
IS  - 2
SP  - 395
EP  - 409
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - The paper presents a “micro” shock explanation of aggregate risk. Shocks are independent over agents, and equilibria are always unique. It is shown that any amount of aggregate risk can be generated by games in which shocks to players are independent. Explicit examples are given, some of which elaborate on examples in the literature. Implications are drawn for factor-analytic methods of extracting aggregate shocks.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1885069
ER  - 



