TY  - JOUR
AU  - Cho, In-Koo
AU  - Kreps, David M.
T1  - Signaling Games and Stable Equilibria*
PY  - 1987
Y1  - 1987/05/01
DO  - 10.2307/1885060
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 102
IS  - 2
SP  - 179
EP  - 221
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - Games in which one party conveys private information to a second through messages typically admit large numbers of sequential equilibria, as the second party may entertain a wealth of beliefs in response to out-of-equilibrium messages. By restricting those out-of-equilibrium beliefs, one can sometimes eliminate many unintuitive equilibria. We present a number of formal restrictions of this sort, investigate their behavior in specific examples, and relate these restrictions to Kohlberg and Mertens' notion of stability.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1885060
ER  - 



